       <td valign=top width=305>


       <font size=+2 face="Arial", "Helvetica"><STRONG>Intel processes promotions</STRONG></font>

        <br>

        
<font size=-1 face="Arial", "Helvetica">
        By <a href="mailto:janeb@cnet.com">
			Jane Black</a><BR>

        
	
	
	
		December 20, 1996, 5:15 p.m. PT
		</font>


    <p>

    <font  face="Times">





<a href="http://www.intel.com/">Intel</a> <a
href="http://www.dbc.com/cgi-bin/htx.exe/squote?source=blq/cnet&ticker=INTL">(INTL)</a> today appointed 11 new vice presidents for several departments at the microprocessor company.
<p>
Tom Waldrop, a company spokesman, said promotions of this kind occur roughly once a year. The appointments were across the board:
<p>
<li> After 20 years with Intel, Edwin G. Bauer will become vice president in the Sales and Marketing Group, responsible for customer support.
<br>
<li> Louis J. Burns has been appointed vice president of Information Technology.
<br>
<li> Mark A. Christensen will become vice president of the Internet and Communications Group.
<br>
<li> John E. Davies has been appointed vice president of the Desktop Products Group. 
<br>
<li> Luther G. Disney will become vice president of Intel's 
Technology and Manufacturing Group. 
<br>  
<li> Edward D. Ekstrom has been appointed vice president of Internet and Communications Group. 
<br>
<li> Appointed vice president in Intel's Content Group is Claude M. Leglise. 
<br>
<li> Appointed vice president of the company's Technology and Manufacturing Group is Bruce H. Leising.
<br>
<li> Patricia Murray, the only woman promoted, was appointed vice president of human resources in November.
<br>
<li> William A. Swope has been appointed vice president of the  Desktop Products Group.
<br>
<li> James H. Yasso will be another vice president of the Desktop Products Group.
<p>
Intel is an investor in CNET:  The Computer Network.
<p></font>

        </td>

<td width=5 rowspan=1>
</td>



     


      <td valign=top width=155>

<A HREF="javascript:OpenWindow();"onMouseOver="window.status='Desktop news'; return true" onMouseOut="window.status=''; return true"><img src="/Graphics/dtn_desktop.gif" width=155 height=70 border=0></a>

        <p>




       


        


      



<p>

                
        <p>

        </td>


