       <td valign=top width=305>


       <font size=+2 face="Arial", "Helvetica"><STRONG>Amelio sees profits in 1997</STRONG></font>

        <br>

        
<font size=-1 face="Arial", "Helvetica">
        By <a href="mailto:letters@news.com">
			 Reuters</a><BR>

        
	
	
	
		September 18, 1996, 6 p.m. PT
		</font>


    <p>

    <font  face="Times">





The head of <a href="http://www.apple.com/">Apple Computer</a> <a href="http://www.dbc.com/cgi-bin/htx.exe/squote?source=blq/cnet&ticker=AAPL" >(AAPL)</a>, Gilbert Amelio, today told reporters he expects the company to return to profitability in the second quarter next year.<p>

Apple, which starts its second quarter in March, expects to reap benefits from earlier cost-cutting.<p>

Amelio, who was speaking at a press conference at the company's German subsidiary in Munich, said the company had cut costs by $140 million since he took charge seven months ago. Liquidity is now between $1.3 billion and $1.4 billion, according to Reuters.<p>

The company had posted a $32 million net loss in the third quarter ending June 28, narrowing the gap from its tremendous $740 million loss the previous quarter.<p>

"The company has been saying it expects to return to profitability in the second quarter, but I don't see progress made toward that end until December," said Todd Bakar, an analyst with <a href="http://www.hamquist.com/">Hambrecht & Quist</a> in an interview with CNET.<p>

<font size=-1><a href="/copyright_reuters.html">Copyright</A> &#169; 1996 <A HREF="http://www.reuters.com">Reuters Limited</a>. All rights reserved.</font>
</font>

        </td>

<td width=5 rowspan=1>
</td>



     


      <td valign=top width=155>

<A HREF="javascript:OpenWindow();"onMouseOver="window.status='Desktop news'; return true" onMouseOut="window.status=''; return true"><img src="/Graphics/dtn_desktop.gif" width=155 height=70 border=0></a>

        <p>




       


        


      



<p>

