       <td valign=top width=305>


       <font size=+2 face="Arial", "Helvetica"><STRONG>Short Take: Navitel announces TouchPhone</STRONG></font>

        <br>

        
<font size=-1 face="Arial", "Helvetica">
        By <a href="mailto:sgalante@cnet.com">
			Suzanne Galante</a><BR>

        
	
	
	
		January 7, 1997, 4 p.m. PT
		</font>


    <p>

    <font  face="Times">





	<a href="http://www.navitel.com/">Navitel</a> announced its TouchPhone,
an Internet screen telephone that enables users to
send and receive email and access the Internet.
TouchPhone connects with an information service
that allows users to configure the system to automatically retrieve
news, weather, sports, and other information.
It also includes an address book, calendar, alarm clock, and calculator. It
will be availabe in Q2 1997; prices start at $299.	<p><p>

</font>

        </td>

<td width=5 rowspan=1>
</td>



     


      <td valign=top width=155>

