<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_23_96/">August 23, 1996--This week, on the CNET: The Digital Domain...</a>Hare leaves with a whimper...Explorer 3.0 has a leak--and a patch...Online travel agents get pressured...                              
                                   
<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_22_96/">August 22, 1996--Domains could get helter-skelter...</a>Did you encounter the Hare virus?...Paper vs. ether in Boston...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_21_96/">August 21, 1996--Netscape throws formal barb at Microsoft...</a>Netnapping odyssey comes to a close...Health care benchmarked digitally...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_20_96/">August 20, 1996--Sprint calls in...</a>Quick and dirty way to stream multimedia...Hacker Kevin Poulsen going through "withdrawal"...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_19_96/">August 19, 1996--When programmer Aron Nabil put up Oregon driver license records on a web site, the reaction was swift and the questions many. The questions might be moot were it not for the ease of access afforded by the Net...</a>Hackers embarrass U.S. Justice Dept...Navigator 3.0 baits the hook...RealAudio tweaks the player...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_16_96/">August 16, 1996--This week on CNET's Digital Domain!...</a>CDA appeal has an echo...Navigator answers Explorer....Digital gets RealAudio...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_15_96/">August 15, 1996--Princeton and ACLU tangle over online politics...</a>Streaming video steps up...NSI tries to sidestep domain brawls...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_14_96/">August 14, 1996--Backing up to tape is great--if you remember to do it, if you don't suffer a fire, and if you have a lot of time to figure out what to back up. These are exactly the reasons Telebackup Systems thinks it has found a niche...</a>Notes gets new Components...Folio organizes your offline pages...GTE, Microsoft work on ADSL...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_13_96/">August 13, 1996--Explorer 3.0 off and running...</a>Nielsen says Web growing in size and loyalty...Cable Net imminent in Ohio...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_12_96/">August 12, 1996--Explorer 3.0 hits tonight...</a>Netscape puts Win 95 on the FastTrack...Microsoft coddling Apple?...

<p>

<a href="http://www.cnet.com/Radio/Rams/August_96/Rams_8_12_96/af8_12.ram">August 12, 1996--Microsoft formally launched Internet Explorer 3.0 the evening of August 12 in San Francisco.  CNET radio was there, and this is what it sounded like...</a>

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_9_96/">August 9, 1996--AOL explains what happened...</a>Crypto classroom: no foreigners allowed...Bikini models reveal Net lawsuit...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_8_96/">August 8, 1996--Lights back on at AOL...</a>Win 95 heading for a soft '96?...Copland: "parts is parts."...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_7_96/">August 7, 1996--It's called Spirograph, and it's responsible for the latest battle over what Java can--and can't--do to your system...</a>AOL tanks hard...Verification for software downloads...Delphi tenacious... about text...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_6_96/">August 6, 1996--E-Data bares its teeth...</a>"Rogue" applet: a matter of semantics?...WebMonkey swings from your desktop...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_5_96/">August 5, 1996--Net access taxes are a hot button these days, though still rare. The access industry isn't waiting for them to become common, and has launched a survey that will be forged into an anti-tax weapon...</a>Scientology vs. Netcom is settled out of court...Gangsta Web sites answered by cops...Microsoft licenses a little "liquid"...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_2_96/">August 2, 1996--It's called the global Internet liberty campaign. This coalition of civil liberties groups is following the world's governments in making Net control discussions border-free...</a> 
U.S., Japan strike vague chip accord...Web pages that handle phone calls...Chips that track scary bags...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/August_96/8_1_96/">August 1, 1996--Net still taking heat for terrorism...</a>Filtering out bomb recipes...Another vote for offline browsing...

