<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_26_96/">July 26, 1996--This week on CNET Central our brand new shows The New Edge and The Web...</a> 
AOL's English-only debacle cools...What has 2.5 terabytes of RAM?...Cyberaccess to congressional papers...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_25_96/">July 25, 1996--Lucent engineers allege job incarceration...</a>Intel postures for lower speed expectations...New flavors of streaming audio coming...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_24_96/">July 24, 1996--A consortium in San Diego is taking a new and unusually open approach to sorting out security weaknesses on the Net...</a> 
Another antitrust suit against Microsoft...Kid's multimedia network coming...Intel sees multimedia this way....

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_23_96/">July 23, 1996--CompuServe sued over flat numbers...</a>AltaVista now scours your desktop...Luxury computer shopping in Manhattan...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_22_96/">July 22, 1996--Where do parents go to figure out what software is good for their kids? Most aren't likely to find that their fellow 
parents have much expertise. Enter Multimedia Mom, a web site that blendsits own parental values with a non-commercial approach and real-world testing...</a>Intel calling...A personal focus 
for the Web...Cell phones cozy up to Net terminals...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_19_96/">July 19, 1996--This week on CNET Central and our brand new shows The New Edge and The Web...</a>Wells Fargo, AT&T want digital ducats...
Videoconferencing to lock out snoops...Software scammer starts one-year bid... 
 

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_18_96/">July 18, 1996--Digital says it will speed up the Net...</a>Corel spills Java on everything...Technology to blow away today's CPUs... 

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_17_96/">July 17, 1996-- Intel news brightens tech market...</a>AOL goes local...Code-free Java? 

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_16_96/">July 16, 1996-- National cyber-terror force established...</a>Netscape OK'd to offer high-test encryption...Big image library gets bigger... 

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_15_96/">July 15, 1996-- MSNBC goes live...</a>Microsoft rolls out a new Java toolbox...Oracle shares its wisdom...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_12_96/">July 12, 1996-- Hear from African American web operators why the online experience is a refreshingly level one...</a>AT&T plugs cellular into the Net...ISDN detente sought in California...Intel will slow the discount race... 

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_11_96/">July 11, 1996-- Online bounty for tobacco villains...</a>CompuServe for the mind's eye...The conversational computer...

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_10_96/">July 10, 1996-- Summer camp is not what it used to be...</a>WebTV closes in on reality...Johns Hopkins expands online medicine...White House won't give up on Clipper... 

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_9_96/">July 9, 1996-- Cable companies want to plug into schools...</a> Security site for kids draws skeptics... Routing your output to Wal-Mart... 

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_96/July_96/7_5_96/">July 5, 1996--  We hear from PharmInfo, the Mayo Clinic, the College of Family Physicians of Canada and Sympatico Health...</a>Microsoft apologizes for "word" associations...AOL settles some billing complaints...British Army recruits online...

<p>

