<p>
<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_95/November_95/11_30_95/">November 30, 1995 -- The Internet continues to be <i>the  </i>financial story.</a> <br> Cable companies to set standards for your desktop PC communications...Steve Jobs's latest windfall dwarfs his success at Apple.

<p>
<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_95/November_95/11_29_95/">November 29, 1995 -- If you thought you'd never get your parents online, SeniorNet can change that.</a> <br> Net access is the star at cable's big show...A student's email tsunami isn't amusing the FBI.

<p>
<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_95/November_95/11_28_95/">November 28, 1995 -- Long distance on the Web.</a> <br> Oracle's inexpensive "Net-centric PC" is on the way...Scientology goes after an online provider...Packard Bell in money trouble?

<p>
<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_95/November_95/11_27_95/">November 27, 1995 -- Bill Gates sighted in San Diego.</a> <br>New shopping experiences flourish on Prodigy, AOL...How smart is the "dumb box" idea? 

<p>
<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_95/November_95/11_22_95/">November 22, 1995 -- A recommendation urges email for the masses.</a> <br>Virgin's online nose out of joint...AOL affects a German accent.

<p>
<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_95/November_95/11_21_95/">November 21, 1995 -- Online pedophiles are reportedly using PGP for a little privacy.</a> <br>An uneasy coalition of companies lobby for parental responsibility...Net stocks continue to defy the market...and a national email system is urged.

<p>
<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_95/November_95/11_20_95/">November 20, 1995 -- It's a "man's world" on a disc</a> <br>Disney sued over re-faxing a hot sheet...A new "econo" line for Compaq...And MSN decides not to throttle back. 

<p>
<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_95/November_95/11_17_95/">November 17, 1995 -- Gina St. John's reflections on Comdex</a> <br>Firewire: the super serial port...Microsoft is down...Hewlett-Packard is up...Shockwave is delayed...Open Text posts its top 40. 

<p>
<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_95/November_95/11_16_95/">November 16, 1995 -- Richard Hart from his limo leaving Comdex</a> <br>Oracle's Internet vision to be reality by February...Sony and Visa get together online...Associated Press brings new legitimacy to the Web...And defining BHA.

<p>
<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_95/November_95/11_15_95/">November 15, 1995 -- Christopher Barr soldiers on at Comdex</a><br>Another show in Vegas gives new meaning to the British phrase <i>naughty bits...</i>  A snappy new serial port is on its way... Comdex winds down...Prodigy to offer SHAREWARE.COM...Federal shutdown extends online. 

<p>
<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_95/November_95/11_14_95/">November 14, 1995 -- Christopher Barr from the Comdex floor, and a new way to cyber-shop.</a><br>Bill Gates made Tuesday morning's Comdex keynote address...Hear how he had less to say about the Internet than some had hoped...An easier way to integrate all those Web searches...And why did Apple take a bite of AOL?  

<p>

<a href="/Radio/Vault/Vaulted_95/November_95/11_13_95/">November 13, 1995 -- How Microsoft creates technology and shapes markets.</a><br>  Around the Net in 30 Days.  Hear how the head of IBM kicked off this year's Comdex show in Las Vegas. His comments focused on the importance of remembering who the customer is...Hear what's
hot at Comdex this year...And does you boss respect the Net? 

