<span class="shorttakes">


<font size=-1 face="Arial", "Helvetica">

<strong><a href="/Perspectives/tc/tc11_06_96a.html">Smart cards not so smart</strong></a>
<br>





The reason I use Visa, MasterCard, or American Express instead of a 
debit card is the possibility of an error. With a smart card, the cash 
is gone. With a credit or cash card, you get to review every purchase 20 
days later to ensure bogus purchases aren't listed. 

&nbsp;--Doug Ross, 
dir@worldnet.att.net, 11/6/96

	



<br>&nbsp;<br>





<a href="/Perspectives/mw/mw10_28_96.html"><strong>Copywrong 1996</strong></a>


<br>





If they are going to make it that difficult to use a

computer, I'll just 
quietly turn it off for the last time and put it away. 

I wasn't born 
with a serial port. 

&nbsp;--Robert Caraballo, susano@bellsouth.net, 
11/1/96







<br>&nbsp;<br>







Fair use is a valuable freedom, and collections of information shouldn't 


be able to be copyrighted. 

&nbsp;--Alexander M. Covan, amc@bway.net, 
11/1/96







<br>&nbsp;<br>







Editors Note: We received many emails asking where to write concerning 


the electronic copyright issues raised in this column. 
Contact 

<a href="http://www.public-domain.org/">Public Domain</a>, 
the 

recently-formed citizens' group opposing these provisions.





<br>&nbsp;<br>





<a href="/Perspectives/js/js10_11_96.html"> <strong> On Bill-bashing</strong></a>


<br>







Yeah! Bill [Gates] gets the bum rap. Has anyone met a billionaire 


they really liked? If Microsoft didn't get the money, 
IBM would have. 

&nbsp;--Jack Olmsted, jolmsted@frugal.com, 10/11/96





<br>&nbsp;<br>





In regards to your question, "Is it a bunch of 

rhetoric or do you 
believe Microsoft gets the bum rap?" I think it's 

obviously more 
Bill [Gates] rhetoric. Frankly, only a company like yours with 

an 
obviously pro-Windows flavor would even bother asking the question. 


&nbsp;--Adam Masri, masri@nolex.com, 10/12/96



