<p>


<a href="/Perspectives/mw/mw9_23_96.html"><strong>Can't fight the peepers</strong></a>
<p>
Sept. 30, 1996 <br>

What law reaches every part of an information network with no tangible parts? 

Your dream is just that. Your motives are right; your tethers aren't 

lashed down to reality.
&nbsp;--Jerry Nixon, jerrynixon@aol.com



<br>

<p>



<a href="/Perspectives/mw/mw9_23_96.html"><strong>Go Postal on Junk Emailers</strong></a>

Sept. 26, 1996<br>


I personally would like to see an open hunting season on the jerks. 

My average is eight spam messages per one legitimate email message 

received.
&nbsp;--Tednlou@aol.com

<br>

<p>


<a href="/Perspectives/mw/mw9_16_96.html"><strong>Spooks in the machine</strong></a>





Sept. 19, 1996

I personally don't think the FBI is watching me, but. A friend said

that the government (or FBI) had secretly installed a chip [in PCs].

I, of course, thought it was nonsense, but not totally improbable, 

just impractical.
&nbsp;--Baron Desmond isc@ni-inc.com

