<!-- ------------------------------MAIN CONTENT---->
<font face="Arial" size=+2>

<strong>Tech stocks float on global sales in 1997</strong>

</font>

<br>

<font face="Arial" size=-1>December 31, 1996<br></font><br>

<p>
<font face="Times">
<p>



<p>

Confusion reigns in technology stock investing. Are PC sales strong or weak?
<p>
<a href="http://www.compusa.com/">CompUSA</a> <a
href="http://www.dbc.com/cgi-bin/htx.exe/squote?source=blq/cnet&ticker=CPU">
(CPU)</a>, <a href="http://www.circuitcity.com/">Circuit City</a> <a
href="http://www.dbc.com/cgi-bin/htx.exe/squote?source=blq/cnet&ticker=cc">(
CC)</a>, and <a href="http://www.bestbuy.com/">Best Buy</a> <a
href="http://www.dbc.com/cgi-bin/htx.exe/squote?source=blq/cnet&ticker=BBY">
(BBY)</a> all warn that PC sales are soft.
<p>

<img height=99 width=83 border=0 src="/Images/Perspectives/Stories/12_96/per_sales.gif" hspace=10 vspace=10 align=left>Yet <a href="http://www.intel.com/">Intel</a> <a
href="http://www.dbc.com/cgi-bin/htx.exe/squote?source=blq/cnet&ticker=intc"
>(INTC)</a> is sold out for the March quarter and says it would be sold
out for the June period as well if it were willing to take more orders.
Pentium
laptops are hard to find, <a href="http://www.compaq.com/">Compaq
Computer</a> 
<a href="http://www.dbc.com/cgi-bin/htx.exe/squote?source=blq/cnet&ticker=cpq">
(CPQ)</a>  has shortages of several desktop models, and <a
href="http://www.diamondmm.com/">Diamond Multimedia</a> <a
href="http://www.dbc.com/cgi-bin/htx.exe/squote?source=blq/cnet&ticker=dimd"
>(DIMD)</a>  is on allocation for some add-on boards.
<p>
What's going on?
<p>
Home computer sales at U.S. retailers have been slow all year
and will rise only about eight percent for 1996. But domestic
computer retailers account for only about 16 percent of the $150 billion
worldwide personal computer market. The rest of the business is booming.
<p>
For example, Wall Street is expecting Intel to report earnings of $1.80 a
share, while I think it may be closer to $2. I expect management
to make very positive comments about the outlook for <img height=163 width=157 border=0 src="/Images/Perspectives/Stories/12_96/per_worldwide.gif" hspace=10 vspace=10 align=right>1997 when Intel
announces its earnings after the market's close on January 14. That will
likely set off a strong upswing in technology stocks.
<p>
This tech market rally can last until March, when companies' quarterly
earnings are reported around the third week in April.
<p>
The annual <a href="http://www.hamquist.com/">Hambrecht & Quist</a>
Technology Conference at the end of April often marks an interim top for
tech stocks. Analysts start to reduce their most enthusiastic earnings
estimates, and investors know the soft summer selling season is just around
the corner.
<p>
But the main cloud on the horizon for the whole stock market is a capital
gains tax cut.
<p>

This is an especially important year to keep an eye on the market during
the first couple of weeks of trading because of the large unrealized capital
gains in many investors' portfolios and the potential change in capital
gains taxes.

</font>


<P>

<font face="Arial" size=-1>

<a href="/Perspectives/Marketwise/mm12_31_96b.html">

<font face="Arial" size=-1>Continued</font></a>
</td>
